note: Former shelfmark: MS X893.7 K84 I116.

msContents.summary: Small, complete copy of the Qurʼān on gold sprinkled pages.

supportDesc.extent: 241 leaves: 156 x 98 (103 x 51) mm bound to 160 x 100 x 30 mm
supportDesc.foliation: Modern foliation added in pencil, upper left recto; catchwords every verso, lower left.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Written in naskh in black ink; pointed, vocalized.

decoNote: Double page illuminated opening in gold, blue, pink, orange, green with text on cloudbands; margin fill of yellow and orange flowers with gold leaves. Textblock of the rest of the pages is gold-sprinkled with gold rules between each line and around the outside. Page opening is framed in a gold rule. Gold roundels mark verse endings. Sūrah headings and text divisions written in gold ink. Readings and some marginal comments in red.

binding.p: Bound in dark brown leather with gilt stamped central diamond-shaped medallion and floral border. Purple and black marbled paper doublure.

origin.p: Copy completed on 4 Rajab 1091 by Muḥammad al-Isfahānī (f. 240r), possibly in Iran.
